{"/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_greenville_ver01/data/sn95047212/00529042334/1958042401/0091.xml":{"full_text":"Paint Brush\nBy GEORGE KAPLAN\nThere seems to be confusion\namongst some of our members in\nregard to payment of sick benefits.\nTo receive benefits you must be a\nmember in good standing in our\nlocal for six months, you also must\nhave a note from your doctor stat\ning that you are unable to work.\nAfter two weeks you receive your\nfirst check. Any additional infor\nmation regarding the fund and\nother rules and regulations per\ntaining to our local can be found\nin our by-laws, a copy of which is\navailable to every member.\nAnother reminder that your\ndues has to be paid and that Mike\nis accepting filled dues books\nwhich he will send to headquarters\nfor verification, also see if you\nhave your beneficiary entered in\nthe front of your dues book.\nLast Friday night we were sup\nposed to act on a dollar assessment\nto give additional aid to sick\nbrothers who are hospitalized. It\nwas decided before any such action\nis taken a committee be appointed\nto find ways and means of how to\nadminister such a fund.\nIt looks like some definite action\nhas been taken in regard to our\nbuilding and also in acquiring\nproperty for a new temple (more\nnext week on this).\nMuch of the last few meetings\nhave been taken up with the H.\nH. Fund. Important decisions have\nto be made. It is important that\nyou attend forthcoming meetings.\nNext Friday night, May 2nd, a\nspecial meeting will be held to\nnominate and elect delegates to\nthe Painters State Conference in\nSt. Augustine on Saturday and\nSunday, May 10-11.\nA short time ago our President\nEisenhower told us of one way to\nbeat the recession was to buy.\n(With what?)\nYTIRUCES is not a disease and\nyou don\u2019t have it.\nYTIRUCES is Security spelled\nbackward and you don\u2019t even have\nit spelled frontward if you don\u2019t\nbelong to the Union.\nThis week\u2019s sick are: A. Ciccag\nlione, W. Wallace, O. King, R. W.\nBoles, Chas. Masoner, H. L. Kelly,\nI. Fiori, Tracy Jones, Irving Sper\nling and Nelson Guyon.\nWon\u2019t you please drive c4< e\nfully?\nThe\nDade County\nFederation of Labor\nRecommends the following\nbroadcast to members of\nOrganized Labor:\nEdward P. Morgan\nAFL-CIO\nMonday thru Friday\n7:00-7:15 p.m.\nWK AT\nJohn W. Vandercook\nMondav thru Friday\nAFL-CIO\n10:00 10:05 p.m.\nWK AT\n9 LdaAwX\nIpMI Whether it's the birthday of a\n1111 l I X^Vgj^HM newspaper like the Labor\nrEW WPw Citizen's fortieth or that\nI \u2022\u25a0Bh'x ^'Hn or Pop, Mary or J ark\nf 111 n fine nay to celebrate the\nWr wf occasion is u ith a picnic\nr, 11 1,1 hotne. tn \\Ps East Patio\n,/WF you'll find every facility for\nBfi. outdoor family fun!\nmany happy returns!\nLabor Pains\nBASEBALLONEY\nNow if the football lovers and\nracetrack habitues will kindly step\nto one side, I\u2019d like to say a few\nkind, and unkind, words about my\nfavorite time-killer and sport, viz.,\nbaseball.\nFirst, let me say that any city\nthat does not support this game is\nlacking in something, and I\u2019m not\nsure what it is, except maybe they\nmiss parimutuel windows at the\nMiami Stadium. When a citizenry\nis conditioned for gambling, and\nprofound suckerdom, it is some\nwhat difficult to keep them inter\nested in a sport that does not pay\na possible profit. The fact that\nall gamblers lose more than they\nwin rarely occurs to your brain\nand-purse-washed playboy.\nThe Marlins are a good ball\nteam, with a seasoned new man\nager, and with another player or\ntwo that can knock the ball out of\nthe field, they should win the pen\nnant. So much for the good and\nnice side of baseball and now for\na few criticisms:\nThere is a fairly large class of\nbaseball fans who resent many\nthings at the games. For in\nstance, when a batter knocks a ball\nover the fence your fan would like\nvery much to see it. However,\nwhen some husky-lunged gent is\ngetting his beer, peanuts, popcorn\nand the like passed in front of\nyou\u2014obscuring the flight of the\nball\u2014they feel that they have\nmissed the highlights of the game.\nSuggestion: Have the whoop\nand-howl sellers of indigestion and\n3460 N. W. North River Drive Phone NE 4-6579\nI. E. Schilling Co.\nREADY MIXED CONCRETE AND BUILDERS SUPPLIES\nTHE FRESHEST, cheeriest flowers in town\nt I\nSOUTH'S LARGEST FLORIST J\nX Miami Miami Beach Fort Lauderdale j\nWORK CLOTHING HEADQUARTERS\nShop Monday,\nAddil)TA Thursday and\nEI^uAI Friday 'Til\n9 P.M.\nBy Andrew J. Anonymoog\nulcers keep quiet during the game\nand permit them to annoy the\nmore intelligent fans only between\ninnings.\nAlso, one has to contend with\nthe type of yamhead who thinks it\nis cute to constantly berate the\nplayers and umpires\u2014and is afraid\nto say a word to his wife. This\nflounderhead is usually half\ntanked when he enters the stadium\nand before the fifth inning is\nready for the drunkometer test.\nSuggestion: Toss the animated\nnuisance out of the park or let him\nreturn to Ebbets Field where even\nthe Dodgers skipped to Los An\ngeles to avoid his ilk.\nAs to the games this season, 1\nobserve that Manager Farrell does\nnot go in for the customary stall\ning. There is nothing more an\nnoying than to have a manager\nchange pitchers in about the same\ntime it would take you to walk\nfrom Hialeah to South Beach. Also\nthe usual conversations between\npitcher and catcher \u2014mostly about\nfishing and the kids\u2014has been\nminimized.\nMeantime, if you can\u2019t get out\nto all the home games and to\ndate they have been GOOD games\n\u2014I suggest you tune in to yippy\nyappy Bill Durney who broadcasts\nthe games via radio. Chubby Bill\ngets real interested in his labors\nand is liable to use ten words when\none will suffice. But you can tell\nthat Bill wants the Marlins to win\n\u2014and me likewise.\nApril 24, 1958\nRecession\n(Continued from Page 1)\nA general review of the eco\nnomic situation was given by Nat\nGoldfinger, AFL-CIO economist,\nat a session devoted to the next\nsteps in combatting the recession.\nResearch Dir. Charles Donahue of\nthe Plumbers and Steamfitters\ngave the point of view in the build\ning trades. The situation in \u201chard\ngoods\u201d was discussed by Research\nDir. Otis Brubaker of the Steel\nworkers.\nAt another meeting Murray\nWernick, labor economist with the\nFederal Reserve Board, told of re\ncent developments in productivity\nand its statistics. Comment was\ngiven by Research Dir. Everett\nKassalow ot the AFL-CIO Indus\ntrial Union Dept, and Research\nDir. David Lasser of the Electrical,\nRadio Machine Workers.\nAgain We Wish the Best to\nUnion Labor\nKenny's Dep't.\nStore\n2167 N.W. 7th Ave.\nBest Wishes\nCIGARETTE\nDISTRIBUTORS, Inc.\nMIAMI, FLORIDA\nMy Sincere Thanks to the Many Friends\nWho Made My Election Possible\nEmanuel G.\n\"MANNY\" ARNOLD\nCOUNCILMAN NORTH MIAMI BEACH, FLORIDA\nGreetings on Your 40th Anniversary\nGEORGE E. BUNNELL, Inc.\n19201 W. Dixie Highway Wl 7-1431\n1007 Blvd. Causeway UN 6-9741\nMIAMI, FLORIDA\nCOAGRA TULA TIONS\nTO THE\nCITIZEN\nON ITS\n40th ANNIVERSARY\nT\nIO NORTH MIAMI: 564 IL 125tk ST. BOLLYWOOD: 1930 TYLER STREET I\n9 MIAMI BEACH: 1526 ALTON ROAD FT. LAUOER^J jI9JX3ir\u00a3AYE^ J\nLABOR CITIZEN\nNowadays a husband and wife\nmust have minds that run in the\nsame channel\u2014or have two TV\nsets.\nOur Sincere Best Wishes\nTo Union Labor\nCRAWFORD CO.\nInsurance Adjusters\n953 S.W. Ist St. Miami, Fla.\nWe Don't\nPatronize...\nRed Adams Bus Line\nShell Super-Store, Inc.\nMiami Herald\nMiami Daily News\nHoward Johnson\nJune Dairy\nBonfire Restaurant\nGulfstream Press\nFlorida Sun\nSigned\nDADE COUNTY\nFEDERATION OF LABOR\nPage 3","height":"27708","width":"18368"}}
